<TITLE> Iqbalur Rahim sent to jail </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 4 (bdnews24.com)- Former BCL general secretary Iqbalur Rahim was Saturday sent to jail after a two-day remand in an extortion case. The director of North Star Resources Ltd, MM Waliz Mirza, filed the case accusing Rahim of extorting Tk 75 lakh. Metropolitan magistrate Md Shafiqul Islam ordered Rahim into jail following rejection of his bail prayer. The investigation officer of the case, Shahbag police sub-inspector Ali Asgar Khan, did not appeal for further remand. Advocate Syed Rezaur Rahman, Shahara Khatun and Iqbalur Rahim's brother advocate M Enayetur Rahim stood for Iqbal. The Dhaka Chief Metropolitan Magistrate's Court on August 1 ordered Rahim remanded for two days. Other accused persons in the case, Sechchasevak League president Bahauddin Nasim, former president of Chhatra League, Shahe Alam, Awami League assistant secretary Shafi Ahmed and SM Kamal Hossain are absconding. In the case, filed with Shahbag thana on July 31, contractor Waliz Mirza alleged that on October 12, 2000 their firm got a contract to supply Tk four crore worth of electronics materials to DESA. The accused demanded Tk one crore as toll from the officials of North Star for the work, Waliz further alleged. The firm paid Tk 75 lakh through cheques at different times, he said. First class status in jail was sought for Iqbalur Rahim on Saturday and the magistrate ordered the jail authorities to take action as per the jail code. bdnew
